---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Training — Cody Smith" description="WordPress, SEO, and AI workflow training built on learning science. Not a webinar — a guided program.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-40 pb-24 px-6 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-1/3 w-[600px] h-[400px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/services" class="reveal inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-neutral-500 text-sm hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors duration-300 mb-8 group">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" />
        </svg>
        All services
      </a>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="reveal text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">04</span>
        <div class="reveal gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="reveal font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl text-neutral-100 leading-[1.05] mb-6">
        Training
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-10">Changes capability.</p>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Your team leaves knowing how to do the work — not just what the work is. Built on learning science, not slide decks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The difference -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">The difference</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Not a webinar.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="reveal space-y-6 text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Most training is a single session where someone talks at your team for two hours, shows some slides, answers a few questions, and leaves. Your team forgets 80% of it within a week. You've seen this. You've probably sat through it.
          </p>
          <p>
            What I build is different. It's a guided program — three sessions over three to four weeks. Between sessions, your team does real work on their own systems. They make mistakes in a context where mistakes are safe. They come back with questions that matter because they tried the thing and got stuck.
          </p>
          <p>
            This isn't because I like overcomplicating things. It's because the research is clear: spaced practice, error-based learning, and deliberate application are what make training stick. Everything else is just an expensive meeting.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal space-y-4">
          <div class="glow-card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400"></div>
              <p class="text-neutral-100 text-sm font-medium">Session 1: Foundation</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm pl-5">Core concepts, live demonstration, first assignment issued.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glow-card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400/60"></div>
              <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm font-medium">Week 1–2: Intersession work</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm pl-5">Your team practices on their own systems. Real work, real mistakes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glow-card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400"></div>
              <p class="text-neutral-100 text-sm font-medium">Session 2: Application</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm pl-5">Review intersession work, troubleshoot, deepen understanding.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glow-card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400/60"></div>
              <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm font-medium">Week 2–3: Intersession work</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm pl-5">More complex tasks. Building confidence through independent practice.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glow-card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400"></div>
              <p class="text-neutral-100 text-sm font-medium">Session 3: Independence</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm pl-5">Final review, edge cases, self-sufficiency check. Your team owns it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Programs -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 dot-grid">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Programs</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">What I teach.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 reveal-stagger">
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8" style="--i:0">
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-4">WordPress & SEO</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Content management, page editing, basic SEO, image optimization, plugin usage, and site maintenance. Your team stops asking you to "update the website" because they can do it themselves — correctly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3">Your team learns to</p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-300 text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Edit and publish content confidently
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Optimize pages for search without breaking things
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Handle routine maintenance tasks
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Know when something needs escalation
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8" style="--i:1">
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-4">AI Workflows</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Practical AI integration for your existing processes. Not "here's ChatGPT, go nuts." This is judgment-first training — when to use AI, when not to, how to evaluate output, and how to build workflows that actually save time without creating new risks.
          </p>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3">Your team learns to</p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-300 text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Evaluate AI tools for their specific use cases
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Build repeatable AI-assisted workflows
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Identify when AI output needs human review
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
              Avoid the common adoption pitfalls
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Readiness -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-12">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">For AI-anxious teams</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Not sure if your team is ready?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-10">
        <p>
          Some teams aren't anxious about AI because they don't understand it — they're anxious because they half-understand it and that's worse. For those teams, I start with an AI Readiness Assessment. It maps where your team actually is, identifies the real barriers (usually trust and workflow disruption, not technical skill), and determines whether a full training program is the right next step or if something simpler would serve you better.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal glow-card p-8">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3">Assessment</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">Standalone readiness evaluation. Maps team capability, identifies barriers, recommends path forward.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3">Guided program</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">3-session training program. Assessment findings inform the curriculum. Built for your team's actual skill level.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3">Advisory retainer</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">Ongoing support after training. Monthly check-ins, new tool evaluations, workflow refinement as your team grows.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Pricing</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Flexible formats.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal-stagger">
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col" style="--i:0">
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Single session</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Targeted</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 flex-1">
            One focused session on a specific topic. Best for teams that need to close a single knowledge gap, not build a full skill set.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-white/10 text-neutral-300 font-medium text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-white/25 hover:text-neutral-100 transition-all duration-300">
            Inquire
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col ring-1 ring-amber-500/30 relative" style="--i:1">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-8 px-3 py-1 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 text-xs font-semibold rounded-full">
            Recommended
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Guided program</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Comprehensive</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 flex-1">
            The full three-session program with intersession assignments. This is where real skill transfer happens.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
            Get started
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col" style="--i:2">
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Retainer</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-4">Ongoing</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 flex-1">
            Monthly advisory after the guided program. New tools, workflow refinement, and a check-in to make sure what we built is sticking.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-white/10 text-neutral-300 font-medium text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-white/25 hover:text-neutral-100 transition-all duration-300">
            Inquire
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-32 px-6 surface-1 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[500px] h-[300px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-6">Ready to upskill your team?</h2>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg mb-10">Tell me what your team needs to learn and I'll design the program around them.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="reveal inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
